fields.description: 1970s Lucite Coffee Table by Charles Hollis Jones. In great condition for it’s age, very light signs of use, no crazying.

A circa 1950s Eames for Herman Miller fiberglass rocker in a Lemon Yellow color.
It’s all original, there are no labels or stamps
But this is a Herman Miller one.
Very good condition over all, does have a crack, which is possible to fix if wanted at a boat repair shop.
It a wonderful vintage example of their work.

1970s MOD bentwood ceiling fixture.
10in x 9in, with a very long swag cord.
Very nice condition, light signs of wear/use
Capiz ball swag lamp. Great vintage condition over all with no cracks or breaks to the capiz.
Mid-century Dowel Console Table circa 1970s, that also could work as a desk. In great shape over all, just light signs of normal wear.
1970's frosted white globe held up by a curvy chrome arm, all standing on a round metal base. Over all in great shape, light signs of normal wear. Globe does have a few minor scuff marks

Stunning circa 19th century Chinese four panel screen, this hand carved 4 panel screen has images of warriors, elders, family scenes, one quite unusual with a mother and child and a man and his horse. Gilded on one side, with red paint on the other. May have been from an opium bed. A wonderful and unique piece from the past.
Very good condition, Structurally sound, there is some minor loss of gold to the edges of the large center panels as well as a few small scratches to the wood on the back side. The high relief carvings are in tact.

Fritz Hansen Lounge Chair System 123 Model E., from Denmark.
Black Wool, steel frame.
In very good condition

Classic Eames design, the 670 lounge chair and 671 ottoman for Herman Miller.
Rosewood paneled and black leather upholstery, ottoman is stamp 1979
Great shape over all for its age, light signs of normal wear.

John Keal for Brown Saltman Mahogany Sideboard
Two cabinets, with two shelves, four drawers, not shown in photos all the way on it’s bottom there’s a
long cabinet that would hold the table’s leaves.
Condition, fair/good. Great bones, would need to be refinished to really bring out it’s beauty.
Made with navy Irish linen, this item has a beautiful goldenrod applique and magenta trim. Adds style to most any living room.

These occasional tables, designed by Ayush Kasliwal, in hand-turned ebonized Beech wood or Teak, combine traditional ornamented furniture elements, deconstructs them, and recombines them in a contemporary form.
One-of-a-Kind white washed wood chest by John Dickinson, circa 1970
Angular, repurposed steel stacking chairs by artist Doug Meyer
Custom ottoman designed by Jeffers Design Group with indigo linen fabric & viscose/silk embroidered geometric trim detail.
Vintage painted metal side table
Vintage brass cow skull with horns. Versatile as either wall or table decor.

A robust study of material that evokes the grace and strength of its equine contributor. Wefts of horsehair are combined with brass and etched glass, implying a structural weight bearing function for the coarse hair.

Lamping: 2 Type A T10 bulbs. Max 60W each. 25W bulbs included. Customization available. All pieces made to order.
Black glaze lamp with harness detail

Drawing on trigonometric principles, these fixtures are a study in repeating triangular and conical shapes. Solid brass, or with hand cast porcelain cones that emit a delicate glow.

Shown in Blackened Brass with Aged Brass connection joints and Porcelain cone shades. Made to order.

Striking like sunset in the Arizona desert. Each piece is dyed, painted, and printed by hand. This is art that you can interact with, objects that function while bringing style and warmth into any room. Proudly made in Los Angeles by Rule of Three.
Picture frame from Alexandra Von Furstenberg, the queen of acrylic decor. Place your photo between the two sheets of acrylic and then snap them together. What a snap to use!
Vintage, clear, round cluster vase made from an assemblage of smaller bottles
A beautifully hand-crafted queen bed build from sustainably harvested and reclaimed woods, so every piece is one of a kind. Bring character to your bedroom, using this piece as a natural focal point.
This hand-crafted piece was built from exotic demolition hardwoods. It features a patchwork surface, balancing urban aesthetic with sustainable design. You can't get cooler than that.
This is an update on midcentury modern, with tailored box cushions and slim, tapered legs... and if you haven't gotten the memo yet, midcentury modern is so in.
A beautiful mix of iron and steel that features an antique nickel finish.
With its rounded high back and swiveling base, have you ever seen anything so smooth? Only a limited amount in stock.
Built from reclaimed pine and accented with a cool blue tone, this is definitely not run of the mill.
Sleep in style in this Art Deco inspired bed. Sleek, linear design married with modern upholstery details makes this a perfect piece for any contemporary bedroom.
Simple yet sophisticated, this full trundle bed will bring a modern aesthetic and distinct style to your bedroom.
Made from vintage textile spools, this wine rack's definitely a showstopper.

The Bihar reminds us of our travels to India, the beautiful colors and hand block printed fabrics. However, these headboards are handmade by craftman in the USA. But, they'll still inspire you to dream about your future travels.
Inspired by a european design from the 1960's, this handwoven chair is rustic yet chic. (We promise that you wouldn't have to put it in an all wood room).
Don't be square. This handsome hexagon-shaped table is made from a solid chunk of mango wood. The top is covered in antique brass foil to create a subtle contrast in color and texture.
Standard design with a splash of personality. Now, just cue up a rerun of ER for the full Clooney experience.
A perfect antique style linen cabinet made with reclaimed wood and iron. Great for creating an old rustic charm into your home decor.

Combines modern functionality with woods reclaimed from former buildings. (oh, If that wood could talk, we wonder what stories it would tell). Anyway can't you just picture this in a designer loft in Brooklyn?

Artist Dana Hemenway takes macrame to a whole new level with these limited edition woven extension cord lights. These unique pieces are visually playful. They add a pop to any room.

Available in custom colors and lengths. These are made to order.
If you're looking for a traditional yet unique statement piece, search no more. This beaded chandelier features impressive metalwork design in its intricate cascades of iron chains. You're so classy.

Whimsical and oh so fantastical. This is what fairy tales are made of... or maybe what eco-friendly homes are made of. Regardless, remember it is okay to have a few daring pieces. It's all about how you put it together.
Add an edge to your minimalistic aesthetic. Note: no animal was harmed in the making of this lamp.

Individual hand-cut capiz shells are edged in silver metal and assembled like a stained-glass window to create these blooming lotus chandeliers. 

If you're interested in the small diameter (13") or large (21"), please contact us.

Inspired by the colors of India, but handmade in the USA. This headboard has the rhythmic shapes and hand block printed fabrics that will keep you dreaming of far away lands.


headboard: 18"'d x 41"w x 70"h, side rails: 9"d x 76"w x 39.25"h
Classic comfort. This winged loveseat has gently curving arms, which give it an elegant sensability.
Pop a cork with this slyly patriotic Uncle Sam Corkscrew. With a bottle opener at the base and a hand-pulled corkscrew under the barrel. You sly dog, you.
Simple and striking, just like a peacock. This rug has a contemporary flair. It's 100% hand tufted and dyed wool. What else could you ask for?

This is a vintage fiberglass shell chair by Charles and Ray Eames with the original Knoll upholstery and a new rocking chair base.

Great condition with minor age appropriate wear.

This is a Mid-Century Modern lounge chair designed by Milo Baughman for Thayer Coggin that reclines and can be used in three positions.  This chair has been professionally reupholstered in blue leather. Great condition with vintage wear on the frame.
This is a pair of Mid-Century Modern lounge chairs in the style of Milo Baughman.  They have chrome frames and have been professionally reupholstered.

"If you look at these chairs, they are mainly made of air, like sculpture.  Space passes right through them."

This is an early Mid-Century Modern 'Bird' Chair by Harry Bertoia for Knoll. Great condition with age appropriate wear.  

Ottoman is 23.5"W x 17"deep x 14.5"H

This Mid-Century Modern rocking chair was designed by Mitsumasa Sugasawa for Tendo Mokko in 1966.  It has a bent wood frame and the original black naugahyde upholstery.

Great condition with age appropriate wear, one small nick in the upholstery on the top edge.

This is a pair of rare Mid-Century Modern swivel lounge chairs by George Mulhauser for Plycraft. They have curved rosewood frames and black naugahyde upholstery.

Great condition with some vintage wear along the bottom edge of the wood frames and vintage patina on the upholstery (one small tear on the back of one of the arms).

This is a CH 34 lounge chair designed by Hans Wegner for Carl Hansen & Son in 1959. This chair was presented at 'Købestævnet' in Fredericia in 1959 and was in production from 1959-1964. It has a teak frame and the original black leather upholstery.

Great condition with age appropriate wear, such as scratches on the wood frame and distressed leather.

This is a pair of vintage Mid-Century bent wood lounge chairs with newly upholstered black leather cushions.

Great condition with age appropriate wear on the wood frames such as scratches.

This is a vintage Mid-Century 'Propeller' coffee table by Knut Hesterberg for Ronald Schmitt in 1964. It has a aluminum 'propeller' base with a gold finish and a round glass top.

Great condition with age appropriate wear such as scratches.

This is a vintage studio craft table by Napa artist, Dane Newcomb.  It is solid walnut and oak with stunning lines and details.

Great condition.

This is a pair of Mid-Century Modern brutalist end tables by Lane.

Great condition with age appropriate wear, such as some small nicks.  See images.

This is a vintage Mid-Century dresser with six drawers (two deep drawers on the bottom). This design was created in 1968 by Raymond Loewy for his DF2000 series X-line.

Great condition with vintage wear.
The bed frame that attaches to the headboard is 64.5"W x 82"L, and the inside storage compartment in the headboard is 63"L x 11"H x 14"deep.

This 'Johnson Wax 1' desk was originally designed by Frank Lloyd Wright in 1936 for the S.C. Johnson Company's Administrative Building in Racine, Wisconcin. The Frank Lloyd Wright Foundation gave Cassina the right to produce it in 1985 (it is no longer manufactured). This particular desk is marked Cassina #0147, Frank Lloyd Wright. It has three cherry wood tops positioned at different heights and a 'brick red' painted tubular steel frame. It includes two drawers and a removable waste basket and two storage racks. It also has polished brass accents. The desk top is 30"H (26"H to bottom shelf).

Great condition with age appropriate wear such as scratches. See images.

This is a vintage 'Orbiter' floor lamp designed by Robert Sonneman. The 5.5"diameter shade, the arc, and the 34"L arm can tilt and turn.

Great condition with minor vintage wear such as a few small scratches.

This is a vintage industrial wall mount steel task lamp. The wall bracket is stamped "ARTISTIC LAMP NY". Edison bulb is included.

Great condition with age appropriate wear.

This is a vintage Mid-Century acrylic Nixie tube clock. 

Great condition.

Oak and Douglas Fir wood construction Circa 1910
Solid, quarter-sawn oak, hand – carved cabinet with wrought iron hardware

Antique Indonesian carved teak chest with secret compartment- small door in top with iron latches, and smaller door down below to the secret compartment. Covered in lovely detail of carved rosettes. located at 2403

Made from reclaimed driftwood that's been sanded, stained, and shellacked. All wood is salvaged from Lake Eerie (which is stamped on the brass, a good conversation starter). Basically, it's a cool way to open a cool beverage.
WILLIAMS-SONOMA
White Wood Frame with Blue Fabric Cushions
Gold metal brass side table with two smoked glass shelves. Rotating top level with shiny finish. Good condition given age and use. Circa 1975 with very faint light scratches.

Rare MCM Drexel Esperanto style wood cane chair with cane intact. In excellent condition with minor chips, scratches, and wear to original wood finish. Upholstery is in great condition and it is a very comfortable piece of mid-century art. Great candidate for a new coat of fresh lacquer. Convo for quote. Circa 1958.
Vintage square table with natural wood top and skirt. Highly detailed carved legs with ball feet. Very unique table with unknown origins. Beautiful patina to wood estimated to be circa 1920.

Roberto foschia sphera air nova chair/egg stool. Designer bar stool structured in brushed aluminum and polypropylene seat. Made in Friuli, Italy. These modern bar stools important design study examples.
Great condition. Some scuffing. Tested & working. One rubber foot missing.
1970s Lightolier Space Age era melamine lamp with a solid cream shade, a vivid tangerine orange body and a simple on off switch at the base.

fields.description: Tripod Chair -Wayland, NY 1939 and Kentucky: Repurposed Oak chairs. Wood finished with Teak oil.
Repurposed push mower and car leaf springs, reclaimed oak flooring and rocker arms. Wood Finished with Teak oil, metal finished with satin clear coat.

Cast in solid brass and polished to perfection by hand. Like a fine wine or your favorite leather jacket, brass only gets better with age. Over time, the polished brass will develop a rich natural patina.
Handcrafted twinkle meets Park Avenue luxury. Sand-cast in solid brass and polished to perfection by hand, these Brass Muse Napkin Rings make perfect wedding gifts.
You've been living under a rock if you didn't know that Moroccan Poufs are hot right now. Serving as a footstool, side table, or extra seating, they're not only stylish but useful.

Think you'd never hear affordable midcentury modern in the same sentence? Well here it is. This side table is handcrafted, made from more economical materials. Luckily, the plywood is pre-finished with a durable material that will provide a trouble free surface for a long time. So, now you just have to find your Don Draper.

Want that midcentury modern look, without the steep price tag? This triangle stand is perfect. It shows some character... because not all tables have to be round or square. Made with more economical material (plywood surface and solid ash legs), it exhibits the same craftsmanship of a solid wood piece.
A nod to '40s Chinoiserie but updated for today. 100% cotton velvet upholstery. It'll surely bring a touch of glam to any room.
Test of big ass product

Leftovers will make you swoon! Receiving 3-5 deliveries a day, you never know what vintage gems will come in through the door. If you're looking for unique and ever-changing eye candy, Leftovers in the place!

Past Perfect is a world renowned antique, vintage and modern collective. Operated by 30 plus independent dealers, you're sure to find something special. Past Perfect carries a range of items, from mid-century modern to antique. New items arrive daily.

Cavalier is a destination for seekers of all that is uncommon and collected. True to a code that celebrates all that is singular and luxurious, Cavalier showcases carefully curated new, vintage and bespoke pieces. It is the exclusive source for interior designer Jay Jeffers’ debut collection of California‐made furniture, as well as the sole stockist for a limited‐edition selection of home furnishings and accessories created in partnership with designers from around the world.

This store was made for home decor addicts. Stop by and see their ever changing room displays, updated daily. You'll truly find one-of-a-kind inspiration for your room or a solution to any design challenge.

Harrington Galleries is a lifestyle emporium has been a Bay Area landmark for more than 40 years. Specializing in estate liquidation, they sell antiques and vintage furniture. These items are complimented by carefully selected new furniture items... mixing the best of the old with the best of the new.

Big Daddy’s Antiques is a retailer of one-of-a-kind antiques and reproductions from European, Asian, and North American markets. Whether you are looking for that funky one-of-a-kind antique piece, looking to create your own unique piece, or seeking an eclectic location for your next event, Big Daddy’s is the place to be.

Every piece we find is a chance to learn about and appreciate a designer or artist that created a beautiful moment in history - moments that we can all fill our homes and work spaces with to create environments full of sculptural lines, rich tones, and unique details

The name Ohmega is derived from the greek symbol omega, signifying rebirth, and 'ohm's law', the measure of electrical resistance. Ohmega Salvage  builds community through commerce by being a model of reuse, recycling and social exchange.

Zinc Details is an independently owned showroom, gallery, modern design authority and essential resource for the San Francisco creative community since 1991. Zinc Details assembles an exuberant mix of art, design and craft that is expertly curated from sources around the globe.
Carousel Consignment has a love and flair for circus and all things vintage. They have collected vintage/antique furniture, art, and decor for years, with a fervor bordering on obsession.
